@node "install" "Installation"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}I N S T A L L A T I O N@{fg text}@{ub}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  * AGA users please copy NewWPA8 to c: This speeds up chunky to planar
    conversion, it shouldn't be used with GFX boards, it will have some
    glitches with overlapping windows, but nothing problematic.
    You can execute NewWPA8 from the shell or your user-startup.
    Using AGA you could try an interlaced screen, giving an impression of 
    the speed you could get with a gfx card.

    NEWWPA8 OR PATCHWPA8 ARE ESSENTIAL FOR CANDYFACTORY TO WORK RIGHT
    WITH AGA!!!!

    This is because the normal OS WritePixelArray8 trashes the
    chunky source. The patch won't start from the WBStartup drawer.

  * The patterns directory holds the standard reflection/noisebump
    patterns and should be in te program's directory.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}U S A G E@{fg text}@{ub}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  Starting Candy Factory Pro for the first time will bring up a screenmode
  requester. The minimum resolution available is 326x300, so everything still
  fits on the screen. Please select your desired screenmode. Using a 24bit
  or 16bit mode with a graphics card will give you realtime truecolor
  feedback. Using an 8bit mode will represent truecolor images in a standard
  palette with dithering. You can use the render option to show the image
  in a better quality.

  You can supply a greyscale picture, preferrably anti-aliased and load
  it with the 'Load Mask' menu option from the project menu. After loading
  CandyFactory will scan the picture.

  Another option is to add anti-aliased text with the 'Add Text' option from
  the projects menu.

  After this Candy Factory Pro will show a nonshaded version of the picture or
  text, anti-aliased if the truecolor option is activated.
  You can change this to shaded or reflective by using the materials window.

  Now you can apply some effects to it:

  @{b}Windows Menu:@{ub}

    @{"    Material    " link "mat" 0}  @{fg fill}Change Material settings@{fg text}
    @{"   Lightsource  " link "light" 0}  @{fg fill}Change Lightsource settings@{fg text}
    @{"   Inner Bevel  " link "bevel" 0}  @{fg fill}Add Bevelled Edge to object@{fg text}
    @{"   DropShadow   " link "shadow" 0}  @{fg fill}Add Dropshadow to object@{fg text}
    @{"      Glow      " link "glow" 0}  @{fg fill}Add Glow around object@{fg text}
    @{"    Bumpmap     " link "bumpmap" 0}  @{fg fill}Add Bumpmap@{fg text}
    @{" Color Texture  " link "ctex" 0}  @{fg fill}Add Color Mapping@{fg text}

  @{b}Image menu:@{ub}

    @{"  Invert Mask   " link "mask"}  @{fg fill}Invert Object/Background mask@{fg text}
    @{"  Render Image  " link "render"}  @{fg fill}Render/remap image@{fg text}
    @{"  Clear Image   " link "clear"}  @{fg fill}Clear image@{fg text}

  @{b}Settings menu:@{ub}

    @{"   Screenmode   " link "screenmode"}  @{fg fill}Selects a screenmode@{fg text}
    @{"    Realtime    " link "realtime"}  @{fg fill}Realtime settings@{fg text}
    @{"     Paths      " link "paths"}  @{fg fill}Filepath settings@{fg text}
    @{"  Save Settings " link "savesettings"}  @{fg fill}Save current settings@{fg text}

  @{b}Project menu:@{ub}

    @{"   New project  " link "newproj"}  @{fg fill}Open a new canvas window@{fg text}
    @{"  Open project  " link "openproj"}  @{fg fill}Open or merge a project@{fg text}
    @{"  Write Project " link "writeproj"}  @{fg fill}Save a project to disk@{fg text}
    @{"    Add Text    " link "addtext"}  @{fg fill}Create anti-aliased text@{fg text}
    @{"    Load Mask   " link "loadmask"}  @{fg fill}Load mask source image@{fg text}
    @{"    Save Mask   " link "savemask"}  @{fg fill}Save mask image@{fg text}
    @{"   Save Image   " link "saveimage"}  @{fg fill}Save final image@{fg text}
    @{"   Save Alpha   " link "savealpha"}  @{fg fill}Save image transparancy@{fg text}

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "mat" "Object/Background Material"

   @{b}@{fg highlight}M A T E R I A L@{ub}@{fg fill}  (change the material of the object or background) @{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  - Edit:                     Select editing object or background material.

  - R,G,B:                    Change the Red, Green and Blue components
                              of the current material element. Using
                              metallic or environment mapped materials
                              this color setting will determine the
                              reflection color.

  - Color, Specular, Ambient: Select Color, Specular (highlight) or
                              Ambient (color of dark areas) element.

  - Shading:                  None/Normal/Metal/Envmap, select no, normal
                              or metallic-reflection shading. Select envmap
                              to use your own image as a reflecting
                              environment (see next option)

  - Environment Map           Filename of the image used as the reflected
                              environment. Very blurry images give the
                              best results. Click the '?' button to select
                              an image.

  - Glossiness:               Change the highlight's sharpness.

  - Load/Save:                Load or save the current background or
                              object material.

  - Copy/Swap:                Copy selected object or background material
                              to the nonselected background or object
                              material.

  When using a metallic material, add a very bright specular with very
  low glossiness for the best results.
  If you subtract the Color RGB values from the specular RGB values
  you will get very smooth highlights.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "light" "Lightsource"

   @{b}@{fg highlight}L I G H T S O U R C E@{ub}@{fg fill}  (change lightsource settings)@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  - Distance:                 Set the distance of the lightsource or
                              reflection. Maximum distance is an infinit
                              lightsource, like the sun.

  - X/Y Pos:                  Horizontal and vertical position of the
                              lightsource. Change it by entering a value
                              here or clicking/moving in the shaded
                              sphere or the main picture.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "bevel" "Inner Bevel"

   @{b}@{fg highlight}I N N E R  B E V E L@{ub}@{fg fill}  (add a bevelled edge to your object)@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  - Bevel width, height:      Size and height of the bevel.

  - Smoothing:                From a sharp, to a rounded bevel.

  - Top/Bottom slope:         Change the shape of the bevel as previewed
                              in the profile box.

  - Carve:                    Invert the bevels height, as if it where
                              carved out. You can make the object darker
                              than the background to make the effect more
                              pronounced.

  - Render:                   Render the bevel.

  When using metallic or environment mapped materials, keep the height
  of the bevel low.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "shadow" "Dropshadow"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}D R O P S H A D O W@{fg fill}@{ub}  (add a soft dropshadow, this will set the background to
                        non-shaded)@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  - Smooth                    How smooth or sharp the shadow will be,
                              smoother shadows take longer to render.

  - Intensity                 Intensity of the shadow, you can fade it
                              in and out.

  - Color                     Change the color of the shadow.

  - Distance                  Distance of the shadow to the object.

  - Render                    Render the shadow.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "glow" "Glow"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}G L O W@{ub}@{fg fill}  (add a glow around the object, this will set the background to
            non-shaded)@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  - Size                      Size of the glow with normal glow.
                              Smoothness of the glow with diffuse glow.

  - Intensity                 Glow intensity, you can fade it in and out.

  - Central color             Glow color near the object

  - Edge color                Glow color as it moves away from the
                              object.

  - Falloff                   How thick or thin the normal glow is.

  - Diffuse                   Different type of glow, normal glow is
                              sharper and faster to render.

  - Render                    Render the glow.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "bumpmap" "Bumpmap"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}B U M P  M A P @{ub}@{fg fill} (add a bumpy look to your object/background)@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  - Select                    Select object or backgound bump settings.

  - X/Y Size                  Size of the bumps.

  - Bump height               Intensity of the bumps.

  - Top/Bottom clip           Clip the bumps.

  - Type:                     Noise type:
                              Normal
                              Fractal (more complex, different sizes)
                              Turbulence (with sharp changes)
                              FTurbulence (with different sizes)
                              Bitmap (see next option)

  - Bumpmap                   Filename of the bumpmap image used when
                              selecting bitmap with the type selector.
                              Click the '?' button to select a file.
                              You can load a color image as well as
                              a greyscale one, Candy Factory Pro will
                              use the brightness of the image as a
                              height indication.

  - X/Y Pos                   Position of the bumpmap.

  - Apply:                    Apply the bumpmap.

  - Invert                    Invert the bumps.

  - Move                      Check to position the bumpmap by clicking
                              and moving the mouse in the canvas window.

  When using metallic or environment mapped materials, keep the height
  of the bumps very low.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "ctex" "Color Texture"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}C O L O R  T E X T U R E@{ub}@{fg fill} (add a color pattern to your object/background)@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  - Select                    Select object or backgound texture settings.

  - Filename                  Name of the image used as a color pattern.
                              Load an image by clicking the '?' button.

  - X/Y Size                  Size of the color pattern.

  - X/Y Pos                   Position of the color pattern.

  - Move                      Check this to position the texture by clicking
                              and moving in the canvas window.
                              Uncheck to move the lightsource again.

  - Apply                     Apply/Remove the texture.

  When using a metallic or environment mapped material, the color texture
  will act as a reflection map, determining which colors will be reflected.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode



@node "mask" "Invert Mask"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}I N V E R T  M A S K@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  Invert the object's mask, creating a cutout effect.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "render" "Render Image"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}R E N D E R  I M A G E@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}
  Reduce the truecolor image to 2 to 256 colors.

  - Number of colors          2 to 256 colors

  - Dither                    Add an error-diffusion pattern to optically
                              extend the number of colors and reduce banding.

  - Background 0              Use color index 0 instead of the background
                              useful for internet (transparant background)
                              and video-title work.

  - Refine shading/bumpmap    Turn on interpolation/supersampling for
    texture                   bumpmap or texture for a smoother look.
                              Or the shading refine for smooth shading
                              and specular highlights.


@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "clear" "Clear Image"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}C L E A R  I M A G E@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Using this option will clear the mask, which will remove the object,
  all effect settings will remain. Now you can add new text.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "screenmode" "Screen Mode"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}S C R E E N  M O D E @{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Selecting this item will bring up a screenmode requester. Supported screenmodes
  are 8bit (also AGA), 15bit, 16bit and 24bit modes. The selected screenmode
  can be saved with the 'Save Settings' menu option.
  Minimum screensize is 336x336, because of the window sizes, hires modes are
  really recommended.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "paths" "File Paths"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}P A T H S@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Here you can set the default filepaths Candy Factory Pro will use when
  opening images, projects and fonts.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "realtime" "Realtime Settings"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}R E A L T I M E@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  These settings are to improve the speed of the program on slower machines
  by giving lower quality representations of the graphics. Truecolor modes
  on 8bit or AGA screens will be displayed with a special dithered mode.
  It is recommended to do a render or turn on Rendered Display in 8bit
  modes to get a better impression of the image.
  On PowerPC machines with graphics cards, all the slowest options can be
  used.

  - Realtime Fast/Truecolor   Select a fast representation when moving
                              the lightsource or modifying colors, or
                              a realtime truecolor mode..

  - Display Fast/Rendered/    Display quality after moving or modification.
    Truecolor                 Fast, remapped colors (set settings with
                              the render menu option) or truecolor

  - Auto Render Bevel/        Render effects immediatly after modifying
    Shadow/Glow               a parameter, recommended only on fast machines.

  - Refine Shading/           Automatic high-quality render pass after
    Bumpmap/Color Texture     moving the lightsource or modifying colors,
                              sizes etc.
                              Recommended only for fast machines.

  - Sliders                   Enable realtime update of the image when
                              dragging sliders. Recommended only for
                              fast machines.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "savesettings" "Save Settings"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}S A V E  S E T T I N G S@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Saves the settings for the selected screenmode, which windows are
  opened, as well as their positions, the realtime settings and the
  default file paths.
  Will be automatically loaded at program startup.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "newproj" "New Project"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}N E W  P R O J E C T@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Open a new canvas window. This will remove the current image and mask.
  You can select the x and y size, the window should fit on the screen.
  The effect settings will remain the same.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "openproj" "Open Project"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}O P E N  P R O J E C T@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Load or merge a previously saved project. You can check the parts you
  want to load, these will replace the current settings. Unchecking the
  maskpath checkmark will apply the effects to the current mask. The
  image settings checkmark will load the invert-mask setting.
  Checking effects that are not applied in the project file will reset
  those effects.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "writeproj" "Write Project"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}W R I T E  P R O J E C T@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Save the current project settings to disk. You can select which parts
  you want to save. The applied effects are checked. It is recommended
  to save the maskpath as well, so the mask will be automatically loaded
  with the project and the effects are shown as they where meant.
  The image settings checkmark will save the invert mask setting from
  the image menu.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "addtext" "Add Text"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}A D D  T E X T@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Add anti-aliased text using a standard Compugraphic Font (CG).

  - Fontname                  Name of the Compugraphic font to use.
                              Click '?' button to select a font.
                              Only the scalable Compugraphic fonts
                              will be shown, because bitmapped
                              fonts cannot be used for antialiasing.
                              The size doesn't need to be set here.

  - X Size                    Width percentage of the text
                              characters; 50 is half the width
                              200 is twice the width.

  - Y Size                    Size of the font, the aspect
                              ratio will remain the same.

  - X,Y Pos                   Position of the text.
                              You can position the text by clicking
                              and moving in the canvas window.

  - X,Y Bold                  Variable emboldening, this is a standard
                              bullet.library function and doesn't work
                              too well with higher values.

  - Shear                     Makes italic text, value in degrees.

  - Rotate                    Rotates the text, value in degrees.

  - Spacing                   Ajusts the spacing between the characters.

  - Style                     Changes the kerning style between normal and
                              design kerning.

  - Text                      Text to be printed.

  This tool uses the standard bullet library functions. Unfortunatly there
  seem to be some bugs in the bullet library, causing some combinations
  of settings not to work right.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "loadmask" "Load Mask"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}L O A D  M A S K@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  Load a mask file as a basis for you object. The mask should be a non
  24bit IFF image file. You can use an image file with background color
  0, or an antialiased greyscale image with a dark background and light
  foreground, for an antialiased image. Loading a mask will remove the
  current mask or added text.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

@endnode

@node "savemask" "Save Mask"

   @{fg highlight}@{b}S A V E  M A S K@{ub}@{fg text}
@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
@{FG TEXT}

  save the mask image you are currently using. Useful for saving the
  mask you created with the 'Add Tekst' tool, so you can edit it or
  load it again. To save the mask created in Candy Factory Pro with
  the project, save the mask to disk and reload it, when saving the
  project, check the mask checkmark.

@{U}@{FG TEXT}                                                                                @{UU}@{FG SHINE}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
